  "text": "Motorola Razr+ (2023) $350 $1000 Save $650 The Moto Razr+ features a sleek design and is powered by Qualcomm's Snapdragon 8+ Gen 1. Its expansive 3.6-inch outer display supports apps and games, and it's now just $350 for a limited time. Motorola just announced its latest Razr lineup for 2025, and for the most part, it's a continuation of what the brand has been doing in the foldable segment for the past few years. While the Razr Ultra is going to get the most attention, the eye-watering $1,300 price tag may not make it a popular pick. Related And if you're thinking about going with the other models, you might just be better off looking into the previous versions instead. With that said, the Razr+ from 2023 is now on sale for a fantastic price. Thanks to this promotion, you're going to be saving $650 off the original retail price, with it now coming in at just $350 for a limited time. What's great about the Moto Razr+? Despite its age, you can see that not much has changed when it comes to Motorola's Razr. The Razr+ was the top of the line model for 2023, and features a sleek design and impressive front display that gives you plenty of screen real estate. When it comes to the numbers, you're getting a 3.6-inch external OLED screen, and a 6.9-inch inner OLED screen as well. The phone is powered by a Qualcomm Snapdragon 8+ Gen 1 that's paired with 8GB of RAM and 256GB of internal storage. Plus, you get a dual camera setup that features a 32MP wide and 8MP ultrawide sensors. In addition, you get a 3,800mAh battery that should last most people all day, along with wired and wireless charging. Related Motorola Razr+ review: My new favorite foldable The GOAT of flip phones can finally reclaim its throne In our review of the phone, we really like what Motorola brings to the table. The phone is compact, sleek, and powerful. In addition, you get fantastic software that allows you to take advantage of the outer screen, making it so you don't have to always flip open the phone to get things done. And while it was a pretty good phone when it first came out, it's now become a no-brainer if you're looking to get a flip-foldable phone for a budget price. Just be sure to act quickly because the $350 price tag won't be around for long. Of course, if you're not completely sold on the Razr+, you can always take a look at some of the foldable phones that we recommend. Phones Motorola Razr+ (2023)",
