-2025-family-hands-on-11.jpg\"/\u003e\n    \u003c/picture\u003e\n                \n    \u003c/figure\u003e\n\n\n        \u003c/div\u003e\n\n\t\t\u003c/a\u003e\n\t\n\n        \n                    \u003cp\u003e\u003cspan data-field=\"label\"\u003eRelated\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n                \n        \n        \n        \n            \u003c/div\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eAnd if you\u0026#39;re thinking about going with the other models, you might just be better off looking into the previous versions instead. With that said, the \u003ca href=\"https://shop-links.co/link/?exclusive=1\u0026amp;publisher_slug=androidpolice\u0026amp;article_name=New+Moto+Razrs+dropped%2C+but+it%E2%80%99s+this+%24350+model+that+steals+the+spotlight\u0026amp;article_url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.androidpolice.com%2Fmoto-razr-2023-350-deal%2F\u0026amp;u1=UUapUeUpU1027159\u0026amp;url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bestbuy.com%2Fsite%2Fmotorola-razr-2023-256gb-unlocked-infinite-black%2F6544832.p%3FskuId%3D6544832\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow sponsored\" target=\"_blank\"\u003eRazr+ from 2023 is now on sale for a fantastic price\u003c/a\u003e. Thanks to this promotion, you\u0026#39;re going to be saving $650 off the original retail price, with it now coming in at just $350 for a limited time.\u003c/p\u003e    \u003ch2 id=\"what-39-s-great-about-the-moto-razr\"\u003e\n                        What\u0026#39;s great about the Moto Razr+?\n               \u003c/h2\u003e\n\n\n\n    \n\n\n\n                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                \n    \n\n\u003cp\u003eDespite its age, you can see that not much has changed when it comes to Motorola\u0026#39;s Razr. The Razr+ was the top of the line model for 2023, and features a sleek design and impressive front display that gives you plenty of screen real estate. When it comes to the numbers, you\u0026#39;re getting a 3.6-inch external OLED screen, and a 6.9-inch inner OLED screen as well.\u003c/p\u003e    \n\u003cp\u003eThe phone is powered by a Qualcomm Snapdragon 8+ Gen 1 that\u0026#39;s paired with 8GB of RAM and 256GB of internal storage. Plus, you get a dual camera setup that features a 32MP wide and 8MP ultrawide sensors. In addition, you get a 3,800mAh battery that should last most people all day, along with wired and wireless charging.\u003c/p\u003e            \n    \n                    \n                        \n    \n    \n                                        \n    \n        \n    \n        \n                \n        \n    \u003cdiv data-include-community-rating=\"false\" id=\"2db4-4ffa-9cf257df2fa4\" data-nosnippet=\"\"\u003e\n        \n        \n                        \t                \n\t\t\u003ca href=\"https://www.androidpolice.com/motorola-razr-plus-review/\"\u003e\n\t\n\t\u003cdiv data-img-url=\"https://static1.anpoimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/moto-razr-plus-review-15-fixed.jpg\" data-modal-id=\"single-image-modal\" data-modal-container-id=\"single-image-modal-container\" data-img-caption=\"\u0026#34;\u0026#34;\"\u003e\n\n            \n\n\n\n\n\u003cfigure\u003e\n        \u003cpicture\u003e\n        \n                                        \n                                    \n                                                                                                                                                                            \n            \n                                                \n                        \n            \n            \n                                        \n            \u003csource media=\"(min-width: 1024px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.anpoimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/moto-razr-plus-review-15-fixed.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=422\u