      \n                \n                \n                \n\n                \n                \n                \n                \t\n\n\n                \n\n                \n                \n                \n            \u003c/div\u003e\n                \n        \n        \n        \n            \u003c/div\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eIn our review of the phone, we really like what Motorola brings to the table. The phone is compact, sleek, and powerful. In addition, you get fantastic software that allows you to take advantage of the outer screen, making it so you don\u0026#39;t have to always flip open the phone to get things done.\u003c/p\u003e    \n\u003cp\u003eAnd while it was a pretty good phone when it first came out, it\u0026#39;s now become a no-brainer if you\u0026#39;re looking to get a flip-foldable phone for a budget price. Just be sure to act quickly because the $350 price tag won\u0026#39;t be around for long. Of course, if you\u0026#39;re not completely sold on the Razr+, you can always take a look at some of the \u003ca href=\"https://www.androidpolice.com/best-foldable-phones/\" target=\"_blank\"\u003efoldable phones that we recommend\u003c/a\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e    \u003c/div\u003e\n    \n                \u003cdiv\u003e\n    \u003cul\u003e\n                                    \u003cli\u003e\n                    \u003ca href=\"https://www.androidpolice.com/phones/\" title=\"Phones\"\u003e\n                                                                    \u003cp\u003e\u003cimg src=\"https://static0.anpoimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/12/threads_smartphones.jpg?q=50\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=32\u0026amp;h=32\u0026amp;dpr=1.5\" alt=\"Phones\" width=\"32\" height=\"32\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\"/\u003e\n                        \u003c/p\u003e\n                                            \u003cp\u003ePhones\u003c/p\u003e\n                    \u003c/a\u003e\n                \u003c/li\u003e\n                            \u003cli